default&#xa0;default3. defaultDo local bodies (including local authorities, local enterprise partnerships, passenger transport executives, integrated transport authorities and local transport boards) have tdefaulthe capacity to assess, prioritise and deliver local transport schemes? What would the optimum delivery body look like?default&#xa0;default3.1 
defaultThe new devolved structures [Act 2009], powers and functions [Act 2011] of both elected
default and unelected
default  bodies are bound to create demographic deficits and also a “churning” of staff and probably in the short term unavoidable 
defaultskills shortagesdefault. However we are partially reassured by the general powers of wellbeing and competence [Act 2011] given to these bod
defaulties and to allow the Secretary of State to “pass on” functions as most appropriate. We would like to see these used to simplify the complex relationship between EPBs and LEPs whose boundaries and functions too rarely coincide.
