defaultWe are concerned that devolving powers to local government could result in 
defaultconflictsdefault (sometimes with transport e
defaultxpenditure consequences) between different tiers. This is currently manifest in the disagreement between the elected mayor of Liverpool and Merseytravel’s Integrated Transport Authority (and proposed Combined Authority) over the issue of the removal of the
default City’s bus lanes
default. 
defaultIt would be possible (Act 2011) to legislate for the election of Combined Authority mayors, which could remove this obstacle.
